From aba0f922b in plasma/breeze (Plasma/6.7 branch)
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] Fix SE_ItemViewItemText: remove ItemView_ItemPaddingWidth, keep edge margins

Alternative to patch 0001. Preserves the 2px visual inset from
itemViewItemMargins (aligning text with the inner edge of the rounded
highlight) while removing the additional ItemView_ItemPaddingWidth (2px/side)
that was discarding 4px total from the text width.

Metrics at Plasma/6.7.3:
  ItemView_ItemMarginLeft  = 2px  (part of itemViewItemMargins)
  ItemView_ItemMarginRight = 2px  (part of itemViewItemMargins)
  ItemView_ItemPaddingWidth = 2px (the removed term)

Net effect vs. patch 0001:
  Patch 0001 removes ALL horizontal narrowing: text rect = full cell width
  Patch 0002 removes only ItemPaddingWidth: text rect = cell width - 4px total

Whether 4px remaining narrowing still triggers elision in real narrow columns
is subject to testing. Patch 0001 is the conservative fix; this patch is
presented as the alternative that preserves some of the original commit's
visual intent (text does not overlap the rounded corner edge margin).

diff --git a/kstyle/breezestyle.cpp b/kstyle/breezestyle.cpp
--- a/kstyle/breezestyle.cpp
+++ b/kstyle/breezestyle.cpp
@@ -1062,8 +1062,10 @@ QRect Style::subElementRect(SubElement element, const QStyleOption *option, cons
         QRect rect = ParentStyleClass::subElementRect(element, option, widget);
         if (viewItem) {
             const QMargins margins = _helper->itemViewItemMargins(viewItem);
-            rect.setRight(rect.right() - margins.right() - Metrics::ItemView_ItemPaddingWidth);
-            rect.setLeft(rect.left() + margins.left() + Metrics::ItemView_ItemPaddingWidth);
+            // Retain only the 2px edge inset from itemViewItemMargins; the additional
+            // ItemView_ItemPaddingWidth (2px/side) is removed to prevent text elision
+            // in narrow columns.
+            rect.setRight(rect.right() - margins.right());
+            rect.setLeft(rect.left() + margins.left());
             rect.moveTop(rect.top() + margins.top() - margins.bottom());
         }

